{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized mask field in AT command test parsers\n\n### Summary\nThe AT command test parser functions in the NAS UE API module were not properly initializing the `mask` field of the `at_command_t` structure. This caused undefined behavior when processing test commands like `AT+CGMR=?` because the mask field would contain garbage data from the stack.\n\nSpecifically, when calling `parse_cgmr_test()`, the function would set the command ID but leave the mask field uninitialized. Later processing stages that checked the mask value would read random data, potentially causing incorrect command handling or crashes.\n\nThis issue also affected other similar test command parsers including `parse_cgsn_test()`, `parse_cgmi_test()`, `parse_cgmm_test()`, and `parse_cimi_test()`.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_command.c`: Added proper mask initialization in test command parsers:\n  - `parse_cgsn_test()` now sets `at_command->mask = AT_COMMAND_CGSN_MASK`\n  - `parse_cgmi_test()` now sets `at_command->mask = AT_COMMAND_CGMI_MASK`  \n  - `parse_cgmm_test()` now sets `at_command->mask = AT_COMMAND_CGMM_MASK`\n  - `parse_cgmr_test()` now sets `at_command->mask = AT_COMMAND_CGMR_MASK`\n  - `parse_cimi_test()` now sets `at_command->mask = AT_COMMAND_CIMI_MASK`\n\n"
}